                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d262">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1881: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-06-13T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 13, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>154. Department’s 138, May 22 [<hi rend="italic">27</hi>]. War Department prefers
                    not to undertake organization of mission to Iran at this time. Reasons given
                    are: 1. Difficulty of releasing experienced officers for such duty; 2. Primary
                    responsibility of British for Middle Eastern operations; 3. War Department
                    doubts that foreign mission could have much effect in correction abuses in
                    Iranian Army.</p>
                <p>However, it is understood General Greely will be instructed to make a report upon
                    all phases of situation, and if he recommends assignment of additional officers
                    further consideration will be given the proposal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
